[signal arg="remember"]
baku: Okay. I know you're in there.
baku: I've been telling myself —
baku: — after the alpha, after things settle, there'll be a right time.
baku: There isn't one. So I'm saying it now.
baku: I've been here since I was eight.
baku: I grew up being the strongest, the asset, the weapon. The thing asssociation pointed at problems.
baku: I got good at not needing anything. Not needing anyone.
baku: And then you showed up  —  got knocked out by a bird on your first day and you just —
baku: — you never once looked at me like I was a weapon.
baku: You asked what they called me. Nobody ever asked me that. You just — asked.
baku: Like it mattered what I thought about it.
baku: Everyone I've ever met wanted something from me. The power. The title. The asset.
